<task id="092" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Update Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1 to register 8 handlers as sprk_analysistool rows</title>
    <phase>4: WP5 6-Tier Memory Subsystem (sub-WP 4d)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>091</dependencies>
    <blocks>093</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, scripts, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies deployment script + Dataverse seed data; no `.cs` modifications; STANDARD per task-execute Step 0.5</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>4-J</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Single sequential task — modifies the shared seed script and applies it sequentially to the dev environment. Prereq for Phase 4e (tasks 093+).</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Update `scripts/Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` to register the 8 new tool handlers from tasks 083–090 as `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse rows so they are auto-discoverable by the BFF chat agent. Each handler corresponds to a `sprk_analysistool` row with `sprk_handlerclass` matching the C# class name (e.g., `"ListSessionFilesHandler"`), parameter schema populated from `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-*-row.json` files authored by tasks 083–090, and `sprk_requiredcapability = null` (always-on per architecture §8.2). Apply the updated script to the dev environment and verify the 8 rows exist + the BFF resolves them at chat-startup.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform DevOps developer. Expert in PAC CLI + Dataverse seed scripts + `sprk_analysistool` row schema.</role>

  <goal>
    `scripts/Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` extended to upsert 8 `sprk_analysistool` rows (one per handler) using the JSON files staged at `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-*-row.json`. Script idempotent (uses Web API upsert via alternate key on `sprk_handlerclass`). Run against dev environment; verify all 8 rows present via `pac data list`. Restart BFF dev instance; verify chat agent surfaces all 8 tools (via `/api/ai/chat/playbooks` or equivalent tool-listing endpoint).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §11.3 (8 new tool handlers registered as `sprk_analysistool` rows; seeded via `Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1`). The handlers auto-register in C# via `AddToolHandlersFromAssembly`, but the chat agent gates tool exposure on the `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse row (R6 Pillar 2 contract). Existing handlers (e.g., `ManagePinnedContextHandler`, `UpdateWorkspaceTabHandler`) follow this pattern — mirror it.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-update-workspace-tab-row.json</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-list-session-files-row.json (from task 083)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-get-file-manifest-row.json (from task 084)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-recall-session-file-row.json (from task 085)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-write-session-memory-row.json (from task 086)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-retrieve-matter-memory-row.json (from task 087)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-promote-to-matter-memory-row.json (from task 088)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-get-user-preferences-row.json (from task 089)</file>
      <file>infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-get-org-templates-row.json (from task 090)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="architecture">§8.2 — `sprk_requiredcapability = null` for all 8 (always-on when the relevant context is present); routing semantics are enforced inside the handler, not by capability gating.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§11.3 — handlers ARE registered as `sprk_analysistool` rows per the R6 Pillar 2 contract.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Idempotent upsert via alternate key on `sprk_handlerclass`; no destructive deletes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Apply to DEV environment only at this task; production seeding deferred to task 104 deploy.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md">Use Web API patterns or PAC CLI via Service Principal; do NOT commit credentials.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
