      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `scripts/Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` to understand the existing seed-row enumeration + Web API upsert pattern.</step>
    <step order="2">Confirm each of the 8 `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-*-row.json` files exists with the `sprk_handlerclass` matching the C# class name + parameter schema.</step>
    <step order="3">Add (or extend) the script's seed-row list to include the 8 new handler rows; ensure upsert is idempotent via alternate key on `sprk_handlerclass`.</step>
    <step order="4">Validate JSON shapes locally: each row has `sprk_name`, `sprk_handlerclass`, `sprk_invocationcontextmask` (Chat), `sprk_parameterschema` (JSON Schema of tool parameters), `sprk_requiredcapability = null`.</step>
    <step order="5">Run the updated script against the DEV Dataverse environment using PAC CLI / Service Principal (do NOT commit credentials).</step>
    <step order="6">Verify via `pac data list` (or Web API GET) that all 8 `sprk_analysistool` rows exist and have the expected `sprk_handlerclass` values.</step>
    <step order="7">Restart the BFF dev instance (or rebuild + redeploy via `bff-deploy` skill in test mode); query the chat agent tool registry endpoint and assert all 8 tools surface.</step>
    <step order="8">Run code-review + adr-check on the script changes.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 092 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1, existing row JSON files</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Extend Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run PowerShell script against dev environment; verify rows</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">scripts/Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1 (extended)</output>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/092-dev-seed-verification.md (list of 8 sprk_analysistool IDs created)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 8 `sprk_analysistool` rows present in DEV Dataverse (verified via `pac data list` or Web API GET).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each row has `sprk_requiredcapability = null` (always-on per architecture §8.2).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Script is idempotent — running twice does NOT create duplicates.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF dev chat-tool listing endpoint surfaces all 8 tools.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No secrets / connection strings committed to the script.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check exit 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Sequential by design: tasks 083–090 author the row-JSON files; task 091 wires DI; THIS task wires them into the seed script + applies to dev. Production seeding happens at task 104 deploy. If `Seed-TypedHandlers.ps1` does not yet exist at the canonical path, audit `scripts/` for a similar handler-seeding script (the R6 pattern may have named it differently) before authoring new. Confirm with /script-aware before creating new.
  </notes>

